sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Intra-Cellular Therapies Inc (Symbol: ITCI), where a total of 1,369 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 136,900 underlying shares.
That amounts to about 57.1% of ITCI's average daily trading volume over the past month of 239,630 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $15 strike call option expiring January 18, 2019 , with 414 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 41,400 underlying shares of ITCI.

Medtronic PLC (Symbol: MDT) options are showing a volume of 25,125 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 2.5 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 55.8% of MDT's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $97.50 strike put option expiring November 16, 2018 , with 6,573 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 657,300 underlying shares of MDT.

And Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 33,887 contracts, representing approximately 3.4 million underlying shares or approximately 53.7% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 6.3 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $170 strike call option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 5,096 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 509,600 underlying shares of CRM.
